-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-BAE Systems, Mediaset
-- 
-- Fri Jun 13, 2014 01:13AM EDT
-- None



June 13 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including BAE Systems and Mediaset, on Friday.

HIGHLIGHTS * BAE Systems <BAES.L> : S&P Capital IQ raises to hold from sell * Mediaset <MS.MI>: Barclays cuts target to 3.40 euros from 3.50 euros; rating underweight   Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Friday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* BAE Systems <BAES.L> : S&P Capital IQ raises to hold from sell * Banco Espirito Santo <BES.LS>: Nomura cuts target to 1.10 euros from 1.50 euros; buy * Diageo <DGE.L>: Barclays raises price target to 2100p from 1925p; rating overweight * Home Retail <HOME.L>: Barclays raises price target to 195p from 190p; rating equal weight * Mediaset <MS.MI>: Barclays cuts target to 3.40 euros from 3.50 euros; rating underweight * Solocal Group <LOCAL.PA>: Barclays cuts target to 0.60 euros from 1.05 euros; underweight * Volvo <VOLVb.ST>: Berenberg raises target price to Sek 117 from Sek 104; rating buy